1. By running the cgi_server.py script, and then calling print(os.environ) on a hello.py script 
2. QUERY_STRING
3. HTTP_USER_AGENT
4. When user click login, a POST method is make to login.py. s.getfirst("username") and s.getfirst("password") then gets the value
from the form's input fields that has the name - username and password. 
5. By sending a response header "Set-Cookie: username={username}"
6. Cookie: username={username}; password={password}
7. Cookie is used to store small pieces of data such as username and password that will make the browsing experience better. 
